Police in the western German city of Essen have ordered a shopping centre to remain closed due to &#8216;concrete indications about a possible attack&#8217;. BERLIN - Police in the western German city of Essen have ordered a shopping centre in the centre of town to remain closed on Saturday due to concrete indications about a possible attack . The current state of our investigations points to the threat being exclusively at the shopping centre, said the police in a statement, adding it could give no further details about the nature of the threat.Germany is on high alert following major radical Islamist attacks in France and Belgium and after a failed asylum seeker from Tunisia drove a truck into a Christmas market in December, killing 12 people.